Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated total cholesterol and triglycerides, indicating dyslipidemia, and a significantly increased creatinine, suggesting impaired renal function. Potassium and chloride are mildly elevated, which may be related to renal dysfunction. Glucose is slightly low, but other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and further nephrological and metabolic evaluation are recommended.
